; The plan.md :331-353 p(1)/p(2) self-supporting-cycle trace, transcribed
; directly: p(X) : base(X). p(X) : p(Y), edge(Y,X). with edges 1->2 and
; 2->1. This is the REDERIVE restore-TRUE arm plus the C_nr>0 firewall
; refusal in ONE fixture (two scenarios via two disjoint node pairs so a
; single oracle run ground-truths both without cross-contamination):
;
;   - nodes {1,2}: base(1) only. Removing base(1) must drain the WHOLE
;     cycle to nothing (p(1) and p(2) both fully overdeleted; REDERIVE's
;     C_r>0 check finds C_r=0 for both post-quiescence -- the cycle was
;     entirely self-supporting, no firewall to stop the cascade).
;   - nodes {3,4}: base(3) AND base(4) (both link-1 firewalled). Removing
;     ONLY base(3) must leave p(3) and p(4) both present (p(4)'s own
;     explicit base(4) support means p(4)'s C_nr firewall refuses the
;     crossing at p(4) itself: SubDerivation(p(4), R) decrements C_r but
;     C_nr=1 keeps total > 0, so p(4) never crosses into D, and the
;     cascade dies at the firewall instead of reaching p(3) a second way).
#message base(u64 X) @differential.
#message edge(u64 From, u64 To) @differential.

#local p(X).

#query p_out(free u64 X).

p(X) : base(X).
p(X) : p(Y), edge(Y, X).

p_out(X) : p(X).
